<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Flywheel Housing</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Verify that the two hollow dowels and the flywheel housing seal are in place before installing
                        the flywheel housing .
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2651321" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figH06/H06010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Torquing flywheel housing mounting bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use an assistant to help lift the flywheel housing into position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install all eight flywheel housing mounting bolts (M12 x 50) finger tight. Then tighten
                    the bolts to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_268.xml" xrefid="t13002" appearance="hottext">special torque
                        value</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install rear engine mounting brackets and bolts (M12 x 40). Tighten bracket bolts to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges2651_268.xml" xrefid="t13002" appearance="hottext">special torque
                        value</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>On engines with a 148-tooth ring gear, leave the lowest, rear most mounting bracket bolt loose
                        (2 or 3 threads) on each side of the flywheel housing (SAE #1A). This will provide enough
                        clearance for installation of the flywheel and ring gear assembly.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
